      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/sqa-mrl5-gradation4",
      "rationale": "At MRL 5, software quality assurance requires Gradation 4: full configuration management, automated regression testing, and documented code review procedures. The solver in use has configuration management and code review in place but automated regression coverage is incomplete, yielding Gradation 3. Gap documented; mitigation plan under review."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/ncv-mrl5-gradation4",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4, including manufactured-solution testing across relevant flow regimes. Order-of-accuracy tests were performed for laminar flows; turbulent manufactured solutions were not completed. Achieved Gradation 3. Epistemic gap noted."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Discretization error assessment at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4, meaning a systematic grid convergence study with Richardson extrapolation and quantified grid convergence index (GCI) on the hemolysis quantity of interest. Three grid levels were run and GCI was computed for pressure rise; GCI for hemolysis index specifically was not separately reported. The achieved level is therefore Gradation 3. The rationale for requiring Gradation 4 is grounded in the absolute (non-comparative) nature of the hemolysis prediction and the Class III device context, but no structured acceptance criteria record has been linked to this factor."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/tc-mrl5-gradation3",
      "rationale": "Test conditions must match the COU operating envelope at Gradation 3. Experimental data cover 3 of 5 target flow-speed combinations; two high-flow operating points lack matched experimental conditions. Achieved Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/oc-mrl5-gradation4",
      "rationale": "Output comparison at MRL 5 requires quantitative agreement metrics with uncertainty bounds (Gradation 4). Bland-Altman analysis was performed but prediction intervals were not propagated from the Monte Carlo UQ. Achieved Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Relevance of quantities of interest at MRL 5 requires Gradation 4: the QoI must be directly the clinical endpoint or a validated surrogate with documented transfer function uncertainty. The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is used as surrogate for clinical hemolysis burden; the surrogate transfer function uncertainty has not been formally quantified. Achieved Gradation 3. The requirement for Gradation 4 follows from the absolute-prediction intent of the COU, but no structured acceptanceCriteria record is attached to this factor — the rationale exists only in narrative form here."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
